    def palindromePairs(self, words):
        """
        :type words: List[str]
        :rtype: List[List[int]]
        """
        
        # Time Complexity: O(n^2)
        # Space Complexity: O(n)
        
        # Create a hashmap to store the reverse of each word
        # and its index
        reverse_map = {}
        for i, word in enumerate(words):
            reverse_map[word[::-1]] = i
        
        # Create a list to store the result
        result = []
        
        # Iterate over the words
        for i, word in enumerate(words):
            # If the word is empty, add the index to the result
            if not word:
                result.append([i, i])
            # If the word is a palindrome, add the index to the result
            if word in reverse_map:
                result.append([i, reverse_map[word]])
            # If the word is a palindrome, add the index to the result
            for j in range(len(word)):
                left = word[:j]
                right = word[j:]
                # If the left part is a palindrome and the right part is not,
                # add the index to the result
                if left[::-1] in reverse_map and right != right[::-1]:
                    result.append([i, reverse_map[left[::-1]]])
                # If the right part is a palindrome and the left part is not,
                # add the index to the result
                if right[::-1] in reverse_map and left != left[::-1]:
                    result.append([reverse_map[right[::-1]], i])
        
        return result

        slow = fast = head
        while fast and fast.next:
            slow = slow.next
            fast = fast.next.next
        
        # 2. Reverse the second half of the linked list
        prev = None

            slow.next = prev

            first = temp

class Solution(object):

        :type root: TreeNode
        :rtype: List[int]
        """
        
        # Iterative solution
        # Time Complexity: O(n)
        # Space Complexity: O(n)
        if root is None:
            return []
        
        stack = [root]
        res = []
        while stack:

            res.append(node.val)
